  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nAfter owning an ENS name for one year, you are allowed to release it. We don't currently support this in our UI, but it can be done through Etherscan.\r\n\r\nHowever, the UI does not respond when a person does so.\r\n\r\nI released my name rachel.stateofus.eth. I can still see the name on my profile afterward, and set it to display in chat. \r\n\r\nWhen I attempt to re-register the name, the UI says that it is connected to my chat key, and thus I am blocked doing so.\r\n\r\nThough it doesn't actually work. Clicking into details about my name showed `Transaction processing` (the release Tx was already complete at this point), and in chat my 3 word name was displayed.\r\n\r\nWhen I attempted to register it from another wallet, I found I had the option to do so.\r\n\r\nPer @3esmit:\r\n\r\n> Releasing does not remove the data defined in the resolver, because users can change the resolver - but we can add that if needed\r\n\r\n![IMG_6404](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/71280775-31d71800-232a-11ea-9b5e-666b66145a21.PNG)\r\n_Profile with released ENS name_\r\n\r\n![IMG_6405](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/71280797-3c91ad00-232a-11ea-881a-242605d7adee.PNG)\r\n_Options for released ENS name_\r\n\r\n![IMG_6401](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/71280809-45827e80-232a-11ea-8f71-02f3377ecb28.PNG)\r\n_Clicking into detail on released ENS name_\r\n\r\n![IMG_6406](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/71280820-4ca98c80-232a-11ea-8f9b-068a3c6092e3.PNG)\r\n_Attempting to re-register released ENS name_\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nWhen a user releases their ENS name, the UI should acknowledge it:\r\n\r\n- Listen for the release event. Again per @3esmit - `can subscribe to the indexed topic about the namehash (not the label)`\r\n- Make the name inactive or remove from profile entirely\r\n- Ensure that user can not set it as their display\r\n- Do not display name in profile any more\r\n- Clear cache that is preventing me from re-registering the name \r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nWhen a 1+ year old name is released, it no longer shows up in the user's profile but can be re-registered if available.",
