    "body": "The reason that data in resolver was not cleared up is because there is many unknown fields, and user might set the resolver to a different address that would fail to clean up\r\n\r\nAllowing the UsernameRegistrar Contract to call an \"unknown address\" (user set resolver) to do \"unknown things\" (clean up user set fields) is not recommended because it opens the contract to unknown unknowns. \r\n\r\nTherefore, the only thing UsernameRegistrar calls at release is the ENSRegistry contract and the SNT token contract. \r\n\r\nWhen I mean \"we can add that if needed\" would be a feature of cleaning up a fixed public resolver address, the fields that are automatically filled in at registration (address, pubkey).  \r\n\r\nThis can be added in the upcoming update of UsernameRegistrar, which is needed because of ENS migrations. ",
