    "body": "That all makes sense then.  Here's my thought on how to approach.\r\n\r\n1) At every login, check to see if there is a ENS name cached in the app db. If so, try to resolve it and the pubkey per your approach above. If it doesn't resolve, prompt the user with an error scenario regarding their ENS Name and remove it from local storage.\r\n\r\n2) Add a new feature in the UI that allows a user to release their ENS name if the statutory year has passed.  When this happens, disassociate the ENS name in the app once the release transaction is processed on the blockchain.\r\n\r\nThoughts? ",
